The '''1590s BC''' was a decade lasting from January 1, 1599 BC to December 31, 1590 BC.
{{Decadebox BC|159}}

==Events and trends==
* ca. [[1595 BC]]—[[Mursili I]], king of the [[Hittites]], sacks [[Babylon]]. This brings an end to the rule of the descendants of [[Hammurabi]] in that kingdom.&lt;ref&gt;http://en-gren.finanzalarm.com/details/1595_BC.html {{dead link|date=January 2016}}&lt;/ref&gt;

==Significant people==
* [[1597 BC]]—[[Aaron]] born to [[Amram]] and his wife [[Jochebed]] (traditional date)

